article.headline: Hawaii 73, Boise St. 66
article.story: BOISE, Idaho -- Bill Amis scored 22 points to lead Hawaii to a 73-66 victory over Boise State on Thursday night. Joston Thomas added 16 points, Jeremiah Ostrowski had 12 and Vander Joaquim 11 for the Warriors (13-9, 4-6 Western Athletic Conference), who won consecutive conference road games for the first time since 2006. Daequon Montreal had 17 points to lead the Broncos (12-10, 5-5) and Thomas Bropleh added 14. Boise State, which beat Hawaii by 24 points on the road in January, has lost three straight and five of six. Hawaii opened the game by hitting eight of its first 11 shots and built a 23-13 lead. Boise State responded when Montreal scored nine straight points to spark a 12-2 run that tied it at 25. Clinging to a 29-28 lead at halftime, Hawaii took control in the in the second half by shooting 68 percent.
